<div style='width:500px' >
<ul>
<li>
To use a single value profile attribute into the query use ${name_profile_attribute} (example: select ... where column = '${name_profile_attribute}').
 To use a multi value profile attribute use ${name_profile_attribute(prefix;splitter;suffix)}: 
  the profile attribute will be replaced by prefix+(list of values separated by the splitter)+suffix (example: select ... where column ${name_profile_attribute( in (';',';') )})
</li>
<li>
Column names with dots or aggregator functions are not allowed, if you need them use alias (as). Example: select sum(column) as name_colum, select column.column as name_column
</li>
</ul>
</div>